        Do Not Forward The Instructions Below With The Application Form.
        Do Not Exceed Allotted ___ Spaces As Field Size Serves A Purpose

        If this application is outdated, please look for PEN-yymm.ZIP on
        your local BBS,  Salt Air  or other major BBS's (where yy is the
        current year and mm is the current month). Old applications will
        not be processed. Applications with altered expiration dates are
        an immediate decline of the applicant.  Look for a newer file if
        it's out-dated. If you would like to be a Super Regional, please
        apply directly with the Host BBS, at the number (& hours) listed
        at the bottom of this application form;  otherwise, file it with
        the hub you intend to call.

       Thank you,
       Bruce Vigil

Instructions:
Please do not forget the "Today's Date:" field in the application header.

BBS:
     Your BBS name, if longer than 17 chars, shorten to fit (leave of "the"
     or "BBS" to accomplish this. 17 chars is all the space we have in the
     nodelist, sorry.

BBS SW:
     Auntie, Gap, Wildcat, PCBoard, Remote Access, Spitfire, Synchronet,
     TriBBS, and UltraBBS.
     (We do have 2 systems that are providing a gateway to FTS, please ask)
     No other BBS software is approved for use at this time. Sorry.

Modem: (Enter the modem for the BBS number you gave in the application)
     B) v.32bis    H) HST    D) D/S 14.4   U) D/S 16.8
     T) D/S 19.2+  O) Other  F) v.FC       Z) ZyXel

Users:
     How many current users maintain active accounts on your system?

Online: (Years BBS is online)
     If over 1 year round to nearest year... if under 1 then give the months.

HubReq:
     The S)uper R)egional or H)ub you wish to relay through (Check Nodelist).
        (file your application with this hub)

Net SW:
     RoseMail, Rnet, Qnet, Cam-Mail, Tnet, GapQWK, Jnet, QWiKerNet or TriNet,
     CNet, Synchronet, M)NKnet, W)Cgate
     No other Net software is approved for use at this time. Sorry.

RoseID:
     If using PCBoard/RoseMail we need the RoseMail ID and Registration #.
     An example Rose ID is SKELETON CREW, an example Registration #
     is 00003952.  If you are not using PCB/RoseMail then please leave this
     field blank.

Rules:
     Check "Y" to indicate that you've read and agree to abide by the Planet
     Earth Network's rules. Anything but Y in this field will nullify the
     application.

Level: Enter Hub or Node to reflect the level you would like to serve within
     Planet Earth.  Initially, new systems will be granted node status.  Those
     that request hub status will be upgraded when subordinate systems are
     brought online.  We support Node, Hub, Regional, and Super-Regional
     levels.  Super-Regionals must apply directly with the host system
     (WLA BBS) shown at the bottom of this file.

